<br>
<b>Method 1</b><br>
<br>
(1) Scout Husman's raid,<br>
(2) Scout Danarin's raid, and<br>
(3) Scout Derrin's raid.<br>
<br>
These are warm-up raids; hail the Scout, give him the item he wants (purchased from a nearby vendor), and then follow him to a grimling camp. Keep him alive until the Grimling Officer shows up, kill the Officer. Loot (some body part) off his corpse, and give it to the Scout to receive a medal. The Scout cannot be charmed, healed, or otherwise kept out of the fight, but has a decent amount of hp and regenerates fairly quickly.<br>
<br>
Now purchase a chest of valor from the vendor. Combine the medals from raids (1), (2) and (3) in the chest and give it to Captain Necin, who gives you a map. Give it back, and he takes you on:<br>
<br>
(4) Captain Necin's raid. <br>
<br>
This one's basically like the first three, but takes place at two camps simultaneously (a second NPC shows up, who you must also keep alive) so bring at least two groups for this one. Kill the Grimling Officer and turn his toes in to Necin to receive the Silver Medal of War. If you lose this raid you lose all your work and have to start again at (1). <br>
<br>
(5) Veteran Vadrel's raid.<br>
<br>
Turn in the Silver Medal of War to Veteran Vadrel to get some war plans. Give them back and you set out on another two-camp raid. This is a tough raid; the grimling casters will try to nuke the NPCs. Bring at least four groups, two for each camp.<br>
<br>
The reward is unclear (has anyone succeeded?), but presumably it's the Golden Medal of the Shar Vahl, which you turn into the General to start his raid. <br>
<br>
------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<b>Alternate Method</b>: <br>
NOTE - you must be level 50+ to use this method; otherwise, you need to do the raids above.<br>
<br>
Ask General Staginar 'What test'. He'll give you a Box of the General's Challenge (8 slot container) which you must fill with the following items:<br>
<br>
(a) Gooplart's tooth<br>
<br>
Possessor Gooplart is inside Acrylia Caverns. Zone into AC and take two right turns until you get to a fireplace. This is the spawn point; the placeholder is the dreamspinner.<br>
<br>
(b) Gizgargank's scalp<br>
(c) Grikplag's skull<br>
(d) Gnildaria's eye<br>
(e) Gnerpokkel's heart<br>
<br>
Overseer Gizgargank, Prophet Grikplag, Sorceress Gnildaria, and Overseer Gnerpokkel all spawn in the mines in Grimling Forest, near the entrance to Acrylia Caverns. All have placeholders. Kormus made a map of their locations: <br>
<img src="http://www.bilderservice.de/ISROOT/Bilderservice/Thumbs/15825/866-2636tldvdaercookbs0851q9751abpogfqkq9fhg-3c16c6ca-t3.jpg"><br>
<br>
(f) Gilgaplank's toes<br>
<br>
Corpseraiser Gilgaplank's room is in Acrylia Caverns, near the zone-in. Hang a right, then your first left. He spawns right in the middle of the room.<br>
<a href="http://home.t-online.de/home/philip-may/eq/acryliacavernsspawnpoints.jpg"><br>
<img src="http://home.t-online.de/home/philip-may/eq/acryliacavernsspawnpoints.jpg" height=170></a><br>
<br>
(g) The husk of the summoned burrower<br>
<br>
The burrower is a timed spawn, located underwater, left of the zone-in. It takes 5 days or so for it to "grow" from the Summoned Hatchling. (The successive spawns, one per day, are Summoned Hatchling, Summoned Larva, Summoned Pupa, Summoned Worm, Summoned Crawler, and Summoned Burrower.) Do not kill the intermediate mobs, or you have to wait for a whole new cycle. The burrower is a level 60+ mob that hits for 512, rampages, and summons. The burrower does not always drop the husk. <br>
<br>
(h) The shackles of a Vah Shir captive<br>
<br>
Go to the high priest's room, and stand someone on the ledge (plank) till about 30+ skeletons have spawned. Eventually you kill enough skeletons, keeping the person on the ledge alive, and the high priest summons the person on the ledge and attacks. Priest is a cleric, blue to 60, slowable, high ac, but not really all that hard. Drops a shackle key, which is nodrop and norent.<br>
<br>
NOTE: There's also an imprisoned grimling in the Cat outpost who will give you a forked key if you ask; this may or may not free the prisoner and may or may not spawn the soulstealer; there's conflicting information in this thread. The priest method definitely works. <br>
<br>
Go over to the Vah Shir prisoner (Trondol Shir) and give him the shackle key, he says he's hurt and he doesnt think he can escape. A bunch of skeletons will spawn, including a "soulstealer". Kill the soulstealer, and give the cat the gem off the soulstealer's corpse. Keep the cat alive; eventually he'll give you the shackles.<br>
<br>
<br>
Combine (a) through (h) in the box, and give it to the General to start the raid.<br>
<br>
------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
At this point, the General's raid begins. It sounds like another two-camp raid, but with lots more and meaner grimlings. Keep the two veterans alive, and eventually kill the Grimling High Commander. Loot the "Arm of the High Commander" and give it to Veteran Cullin. Cullin then gives you the magical acrylia obelisk to give to the General. <br>
<br>
Presumably the General then makes you a key to the Grimling Castle.<br>
